\layout Title

Modular Fractal Measures
\layout Author

Linas Vepstas <linas@linas.org>
\layout Date

12 October 2004
\layout Abstract

In this breif note, we review the connection between the distribution of
 the Farey fractions on the real number line, and the derivative of the
 Minkowski Question Mark function.
 We point out that the derivivative of the question mark can also be obtained
 as the limiting behaviour of a modular form.
 Modular forms are analytic functions that are closely related to elliptic
 functions, and have a particular kind of modular group symmetry.
 
\layout Abstract

This paper is part of a set of chapters that explore the relationship between
 the real numbers, the modular group, and fractals.
